Seasoned American athletes in this context refer to players over 22 years old; a half-season of matches is more than 50 games; overall effectiveness is measured by the efficiency rating. The details include both general and game-specific stats, as well as personal and financial information. The focus is on the top 10 most efficient players.;
"Seasoned" implies experience and age typically beyond the typical draft age (20-21 years old).;
"Financial contracts" refer to the terms of employment, including the start and end dates of their contracts, annual salary, and guaranteed salary. It gives an insight into their financial standing with the team.;
"Game-specific stats" include performance metrics from specific games, such as field goals, free throws, rebounds, and assists. These provide a snapshot of performance in recent games.;
"Acolades received" include honors and awards like MVP, All-Star, or Rookie of the Year, highlighting achievements and recognition in the league.;

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT a.player_id)
FROM awards a
JOIN injuries i ON a.player_id = i.player_id;

SELECT player_id, age, height, weight, team_id, position, jersey_number, draft_year, draft_round, draft_pick, nationality, college
FROM players
WHERE EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM injuries WHERE injuries.player_id = players.player_id);
